item.title: Dungeoneering.java
item.dc:creator: @collin123456 collin123456
item.description:
@collin123456 wrote:

[quote=“Mod Whip, post:4, topic:394046”]=P you’re kidding right? First off you would need a server that loads the client for dung maps/items/npcs/objects. Or you could add those into a 317 client, but It wouldn’t exactly be a good way to do things =p. Then you’d probably wanna add player clipping, npc loading, and basic packets for wielding items, attacking npcs, that kinda stuff. Skipping forward a bit, you’d have to add dungeoneering itself, having instanced situations, 60 floors, 6 complexities… a party system… Go get a masters degree in computer science then go back and try it again =)

Would be pretty hard to do, my point is.[/quote]
not exactly like dungeoneering, as i know that would take a professional, i was kinda thinking of copying the slayer bit over and using that for a dungeoneering skill (or even renaming it, but id have an even harder time doing that) and 2 slayers would be a fail imo… im open to suggestions of what i should change it too, just a blank box in the middle looks bad
